Proposed Solution:
Plan
- Use rotation about c by angle θ: w = c + e^{iθ}(z - c) with θ = π/4.
- Compute z − c, multiply by e^{iπ/4}, then add c.

Solution steps
- z − c = (2 + √2) − (3 + 3√2)i − (2 − 3i) = √2 − 3√2 i = √2(1 − 3i).
- e^{iπ/4} = (1 + i)/√2, so e^{iπ/4}(z − c) = (1/√2)(1 + i) · √2(1 − 3i) = (1 + i)(1 − 3i) = 4 − 2i.
- Therefore w = c + e^{iπ/4}(z − c) = (2 − 3i) + (4 − 2i) = 6 − 5i.

